    "texts": [
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Identification features",
            "shortText": "<p>Fairly delicate and common species which forms dense branching clumps in pools in the lower intertidal and shallow subtidal. The main axes are flattened, fairly ‘woody’ and microscopically divided into segments (but these are hard to see in the field) and give off smaller flattened branches alternately to the left and right, these laterals rebranching 2-3 times before coming to pointed ends. Colour dark brown, sometimes almost black.&nbsp;</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_1_7907",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Adult size",
            "shortText": "<p>Clumps can be up to 200 mm tall, but often much smaller. Blades only about 1.5 mm wide.</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_2_7908",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Distribution",
            "shortText": "<p><u>Global:</u> Namibia, South Africa, Oman, Pakistan, Amsterdam and St Paul Islands.</p><p><u>Local/Regional: </u>Namibia to Port Edward in southern KwaZulu-Natal.</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_3_7909",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Biology",
            "shortText": "<p>Can be very common in intertidal, especially in wave-swept areas, where sometimes forming a distinct zone in lowshore pools. Appearance and size quite variable and lower branches may be worn off in some specimens.</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_4_7910",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Food / prey",
            "shortText": "<p>Photosynthetic.</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_5_7911",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Reproduction",
            "shortText": "<p>Tetrasporangia are borne in apical parts of lateral branches.</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_6_7912",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
            "taxonTextType": "Similar species",
            "shortText": "<p>There are several other species of this genus in the region. Of these <i>P. spinifera</i> has round, not flattened axes and <i>P. stegengae</i> wider, more flattened fan-like branches. Undescribed species probably also present (see <i>Pterosiphonia </i>sp. entry).</p>",
            "shortTextKey": "taxon_text_7_7913",
            "longText": null,
            "longTextKey": null,
            "images": []
        },
        {
